data.name: PortForwardingDocumentDescriptionLabel.Text
data.value: When opening a port forwarding tunnel, this specifies the document name to use, based on what your system administrator setup under your profile. Defaults to the AWS-StartPortForwardingSession document if left blank.

data.name: OneTimePasswordDescriptionLabel.Text
data.value: This is used for automatically entering your MFA token value when establishing a connection to an EC2 instance, assuming your account is MFA protected. Applies to the Profile Name - Admin if populated, otherwise falls back to the standard Profile Name field.

data.name: WhatsThisForLabel.Text
data.value: If you have a separate profile for administration level operations that requires an additional level of security (ex: multi-factor authentication), you can put it here. If not, leave empty and we will use the primary Profile Name field.

data.name: PurgeTempFilesWarningLabel.Text
data.value: WARNING! This will run multiple deletion commands on your system to delete any and all files/folders in your Temporary ASP.NET Files folder. It is safe, but be aware you are performing a destructive operation on your machine.

data.name: CloudflareTunnelDescriptionLabel.Text
data.value: Need to create a tunnel from the internet to your local development environment? Use this one-click solution to start up a new tunnel. By default, this will route to https://localhost:44300, however you can override the port number below. Once the tunnel is created, the tunnel name will be output in the console window.
